h]], American-French publisher, founded [[Shakespeare and Company (bookstore)|Shakespeare and Company]] (d. 1962)\n*[[1894]] &ndash; [[Osa Johnson]], American director and explorer (d. 1953)\n*[[1898]] &ndash; [[Arnold Chikobava]], Georgian linguist and philologist (d. 1985)\n*  1898   &ndash; [[Reginald Marsh (artist)|Reginald Marsh]], French-American painter and illustrator (d. 1954)\n*[[1899]] &ndash; [[K. C. Irving]], Canadian businessman, founded [[Irving Oil]] (d. 1992)\n*[[1901]] &ndash; [[Sid Atkinson]], South African hurdler and long jumper (d. 1977)\n*[[1903]] &ndash; [[Adolph Gottlieb]], American painter and sculptor (d. 1974)\n*[[1904]] &ndash; [[Doris Eaton Travis]], American actress and dancer (d. 2010)\n*[[1905]] &ndash; [[Raymond Aron]], French journalist, sociologist, and philosopher (d. 1983)\n*[[1906]] &ndash; [[Ulvi Cemal Erkin]], Turkish composer and educator (d. 1972)\n*  1906   &ndash; [[Faz\u0131l K\u00fc\u00e7\u00fck]], Cypriot journalist and politician (d. 1984)\n*[[1908]] &ndash; [[Ed Heinemann]], American engineer (d. 1991)\n*  1908   &ndash; [[Maurice Merleau-Ponty]], French philosopher and academic (d. 1961)\n*  1908   &ndash; [[Phil Vincent|Philip Conrad Vincent]], English engineer and businessman, founded [[Vincent Motorcycles]] (d. 1979)\n*[[1911]] &ndash; [[Akira Yoshizawa]], Japanese origamist (d. 2005)\n*[[1912]] &ndash; [[Cliff Bastin]], English footballer (d. 1991)\n*  1912   &ndash; [[Les Brown (bandleader)|Les Brown]], American saxophonist, composer, and bandleader (d. 2001)\n*  1912   &ndash; [[W. Graham Claytor, Jr.]] American lieutenant, lawyer, and politician, 15th [[United States Secretary of the Navy]] (d. 1994)\n*  1912   &ndash; [[W. Willard Wirtz]], American lawyer and politician, 10th [[United States Secretary of Labor]] (d. 2010)\n*[[1914]] &ndash; [[Lee Hays]], American singer-songwriter (d. 1981)\n*  1914   &ndash; [[Bill Owen (actor)|Bill Owen]], English actor and songwriter (d. 1999)\n*  1914   &ndash; [[Lee Petty]], American race car driver and businessman, founded [[Petty Enterprises]] (d. 2000)\n*[[1915]] &ndash; [[Alexander Brott]], Canadian violinist, composer, and conductor (d. 2005)\n*[[1916]] &ndash; [[Horton Foote]], American author, playwright, and screenwriter (d. 2009)<ref name=\"BEagle\" />\n*[[1917]] &ndash; [[Alan Smith (RAF officer)|Alan Smith]], English lieutenant and pilot (d. 2013)\n*[[1918]] &ndash; [[Zoia Horn]], American librarian (d. 2014)<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://viaf.org/viaf/74659699|title=Virtual International Authority File|last=Horn|first=Zoia|date=|website=|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180719084405/https://viaf.org/viaf/74659699/|archive-date=2018-07-19|access-date=|url-status=live}}</ref> \n*  1918   &ndash; [[Dennis Patrick]], American actor and director (d. 2002)\n*[[1919]] &ndash; [[Max Shulman]], American author and screenwriter (d. 1988)\n*[[1920]] &ndash; [[Hank Ketcham]], American author and cartoonist, created ''[[Dennis the Menace (U.S. comics)|Dennis the Menace]]'' (d. 2001)\n*  1920   &ndash; [[Dorothy Tyler-Odam]], English high jumper (d. 2014)\n*[[1921]] &ndash; [[S. Truett Cathy]], American businessman, founded [[Chick-fil-A]] (d. 2014)\n*  1921   &ndash; [[Ada Louise Huxtable]], American author and critic (d. 2013)\n*[[1922]] &ndash; [[Les Baxter]], American pianist and composer (d. 1996)\n*  1922   &ndash; [[China Zorrilla]], Uruguayan actress, director, and producer (d. 2014)\n*[[1923]] &ndash; [[Diane Arbus]], American photographer (d. 1971)\n*[[1925]] &ndash; [[William Clay Ford, Sr.]], American businessman (d. 2014)\n*  1925   &ndash; [[Joseph A. Unanue]], American sergeant and businessman (d. 2013)\n*[[1926]] &ndash; [[Fran\u00e7ois Morel]], Canadian pianist, composer, conductor, and educator (d. 2018)\n*[[1928]] &ndash; [[Frank Borman]], American colonel, pilot, and astronaut<ref name=\"BEagle\" />\n*  1928   &ndash; [[F\u00e9lix Rodr\u00edguez de la Fuente]], Spanish environmentalist (d. 1980)\n*[[1929]] 