 Sang what on Broadway, 1866-1996: The singers (L-Z) |date=2006 |publisher=McFarland & Company, Publishers |isbn=978-0-7864-2190-9 |page=551 |url=https://books.google.se/books?id=oCoKAQAAMAAJ |accessdate=5 April 2020 |language=en}}</ref>\n*[[1944]] &ndash; [[Boris Brott]], Canadian composer and conductor<ref>{{cite book |last1=Sharpe |first1=Roderick L. |last2=Stierman |first2=Jeanne Koekkoek |title=Maestros in America: Conductors in the 21st Century |date=2008 |publisher=Scarecrow Press |isbn=978-1-4616-6948-7 |page=30 |url=https://books.google.se/books?id=OTEROkR8d-AC&pg=PA30&redir_esc=y#v=onepage&q&f=false |accessdate=5 April 2020 |language=en}}</ref>\n*  1944   &ndash; [[V\u00e1clav Nedomansk\u00fd]], Czech ice hockey player and manager<ref>{{cite web |title=Vaclav Nedomansky Stats |url=https://www.hockey-reference.com/players/n/nedomva01.html |website=Hockey-Reference.com |accessdate=5 April 2020 |language=en}}</ref>\n*  1944   &ndash; [[Bobby Smith (footballer, born 1944)|Bobby Smith]], English footballer and manager<ref>{{cite web |title=OTD: March 14 |url=https://www.scunthorpe-united.co.uk/news/2020/march/otd-march-14/ |website=www.scunthorpe-united.co.uk |accessdate=7 March 2020 |language=en-gb}}</ref>\n*  1944   &ndash; [[Tom Stannage]], Australian historian and academic (d. 2012)<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Bobbie Oliver |title=Charles Thomas (Tom) Stannage, 1944-2012 |journal=Labour History |date=2013 |issue=104 |pages=225 |doi=10.5263/labourhistory.104.0225 |accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref>\n*[[1945]] &ndash; [[Jasper Carrott]], English comedian, actor, and game show host<ref>{{cite web |title=Jasper Carrott |url=https://www.oxfordreference.com/view/10.1093/oi/authority.20110803095551719 |website=Oxford Reference |accessdate=4 April 2020 |language=en |doi=10.1093/oi/authority.20110803095551719}}</ref>\n*  1945   &ndash; [[Michael Martin Murphey]], American singer-songwriter and guitarist<ref>{{cite book |last1=McCall |first1=Michael |last2=Rumble |first2=