{"title_page": "Hans Weilb\u00e4cher", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Hans Weilb\u00e4cher\n| fullname = Hans Weilb\u00e4cher\n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1933|10|23}}\n| birth_place =[[Germany]]\n| height = \n| currentclub = Retired\n| position = [[Midfielder]]\n| youthyears1 = 1945\u20131952 | youthyears2 =1952\u20131953\n| youthclubs1 = SV Hattersheim | youthclubs2 =[[Eintracht Frankfurt]]\n| years1= 1952\u20131965\n| clubs1= [[Eintracht Frankfurt]]\n| caps1= 241 | goals1 = 48\n| nationalyears1= 1955\n| nationalteam1= [[Germany national football team|West Germany]]\n| nationalcaps1= 1 | nationalgoals1 = 0\n}}\n'''Hans Weilb\u00e4cher''' (born 23 October 1933) is a former German [[football (soccer)|football]] player. He was capped once for Germany in 1955 against [[Republic of Ireland national football team|Republic of Ireland]].<ref>{{WorldFootball.net}}</ref> With his club side [[Eintracht Frankfurt]], he won the German championship in 1959 and reached the European Cup final in the following year against Real Madrid which the ''Eagles'' lost.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.eintracht-archiv.de/weilbaecherh.html Hans Weilb\u00e4cher at eintracht-archiv.de]\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Weilbacher, Hans}}\n[[Category:1933 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:German footballers]]\n[[Category:Germany international footballers]]\n[[Category:Eintracht Frankfurt players]]\n[[Category:Association football midfielders]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Hans Weilb\u00e4cher\n| fullname = Hans Weilb\u00e4cher\n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1933|10|23}}\n| birth_place =[[Germany]]\n| height = \n| currentclub = Retired\n| position = [[Midfielder]]\n| youthyears1 = 1945\u20131952 | youthyears2 =1952\u20131953\n| youthclubs1 = SV Hattersheim | youthclubs2 =[[Eintracht Frankfurt]]\n| years1= 1952\u20131965\n| clubs1= [[Eintracht Frankfurt]]\n| caps1= 241 | goals1 = 48\n| nationalyears1= 1955\n| nationalteam1= [[Germany national football team|West Germany]]\n| nationalcaps1= 1 | nationalgoals1 = 0\n| pcupdate = July 14, 2007\n| ntupdate = July 14, 2007\n}}\n'''Hans Weilb\u00e4cher''' (born October 23, 1933) is a former German [[football (soccer)|football]] player. He was capped once for Germany in 1955 against [[Republic of Ireland national football team|Republic of Ireland]]. With his club side [[Eintracht Frankfurt]], he won the German championship in 1959 and reached the European Cup final in the following year against Real Madrid which the ''Eagles'' lost.\n\n== Sources ==\n[http://www.eintracht-archiv.de/weilbaecherh.html Hans Weilb\u00e4cher at eintracht-archiv.de]\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Weilbacher, Hans}}\n[[Category:1933 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:German footballers]]\n[[Category:Germany international footballers]]\n[[Category:Eintracht Frankfurt players]]\n[[Category:Association football midfielders]]\n", "name_user": "S.A. Julio", "label": "safe", "comment": "cleanup", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hans_Weilb%C3%A4cher"}
